HEADWORD: Faldfee
<hw>Fald"fee`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>fald</ets>
(E.<ets>fold</ets>) + E. <ets>fee</ets>. See <er>Faldage</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A fee or rent paid by a tenant for the
privilege of faldage on his own ground.</def>
<rj><au>Blount.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

